node.text:
This Juneteenth we wrap on our Beauty of Becoming series with the woman who created and directed the short films, Oge Egbuonu. Through telling stories that celebrate the people that society often casts aside, while embracing the unfolding chapters of her own, Oge Egbuonu is becoming. 

Created and Directed by @ogetheyogi
Music by @phantogram

[Video: Oge is sitting in front of a brown background and green leaves with pink and red floral arrangements. She is wearing a black denim shirt with her name embroidered above the front left breast pocket and black denim jeans. Shots of her walking around in a flower labyrinth of various colors and sitting at a wooden desk on a wooden writing on a piece of paper are shown throughout the video.]

node.text:
Through breaking down barriers, making history, and pioneering for other LGBTQI+ models and actresses, @leynabloom is becoming. 

Created and Directed by @ogetheyogi
Music by @phantogram

[Video: Leyna is sitting in front of a brown background and green leaves with pink and red floral arrangements. She is wearing a denim jumpsuit with her name embroidered above the front left breast pocket and tied together with a black leather belt. Shots of her walking around in a flower labyrinth of various colors and sitting at a wooden desk on a wooden writing on a piece of paper are shown throughout the video.]

This year, more than ever, we need to amplify—and listen to—Asian American Pacific Islander stories. In honor of AAPI Heritage Month, Levi’s® is partnering with employees and friends in the community to create 15 customized Trucker Jackets that celebrate their histories.

Directed by @yongwkim.

node.text:
Through a continued dedication to advancing civil rights while inspiring today’s activists to step up and speak out, @carlosmmontes is becoming. 

Created and Directed by @ogetheyogi
Music by @phantogram

***
[Video: Carlos is sitting in front of a brown background behind a gold frame with pastel colored florals. He is wearing a beige long sleeve button down shirt, a black t-shirt with the Mexico flag printed on the front, paired with black framed glasses and a beige hat. Shots of him walking around in a flower labyrinth of various colors and sitting at a wooden desk on a wooden writing on a piece of paper are shown throughout the video. Photos of a younger Carlos are also shown throughout the video.]

node.text:
The Grateful Dead live album known as “Skull & Roses” was released in 1971 and it’s been blowing minds ever since. Tomorrow, we’re dropping a collab featuring the iconic Skull and Roses artwork. Get on the bus and take a very interesting trip with us.
TM & ® 2021 GDP

node.text: The Tailor Profile Series made a stop at our Levi’s® store in Portland, OR. Lead Tailor, Emily Carrig sat down with us for a little Q&A and shared some of her recent work, passions, and how she got started as a tailor. Head over to our blog to read the interview! LINK IN BIO.

node.text:
Not your dad’s chinos. Meet our two newest styles that put an ultra relaxed spin on the classic chino silhouette. 
Shop our XX Stay Baggy and XX Chino Relaxed Taper at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Levi's on July 21, 2021 tagging @edwardcooke, and @chris_dalglish. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text.

node.text:
“In London, you don’t go home after work to change for a night out, so it doesn’t matter if you’re in the pub, club or office—you wear the same thing. So it ends up being a nice balance of casual and cool that works anytime, anywhere.” — Christopher Dalglish, PR Specialist Read the latest edition of our What We’re Wearing series at the link in our bio.

📸: @edwardcooke

node.text:
We’re giving away these one-of-a-kind airbrushed truckers that we created in partnership with @braverobot for National Ice Cream Day on July 18th 🍦 Head to stories to see how you can win one and if you’re in NYC find the Brave Robot Ice Cream truck: 
 
Saturday, July 17th
Levi’s® Williamsburg Store
120 N. 4thStreet
Starting at 11am
 
Sunday, July 18th
Levi’s® Soho Store
495 Broadway
Starting at 11am
 
*Fans must sign up between 7/16 – 7/18, while supplies last.
